My analysis is correct. The section starting at line 286 is labeled "Non win8 machines which need native backlight nevertheless" which exactly describes the Acer TravelMate 5735Z case - it's an older non-Win8 machine that needs native backlight to work.

The fix would be adding a new entry like:
```c
{
 /* https://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=207835 */
 .callback = video_detect_force_native,
 .ident = "Acer TravelMate 5735Z",
 .matches = {
    DMI_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "Acer"),
    DMI_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "TravelMate 5735Z"),
    },
},
```

